Bayer Reaches Agreement on Brazilian Hybrid Rice License Rights

-- B y   M a r i a j o s e   V e r a
-- 
2011-09-28T12:06:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/bayer-reaches-agreement-on-brazilian-hybrid-rice-license-rights.html
Bayer CropScience  reached an
agreement granting it exclusive worldwide license rights to the
rice breeding program of the Brazilian company Fazenda Ana
Paula, the company said in an e-mailed statement today. Bayer
CropScience said the agreement will enable it to expand its
breeding capability and development of hybrid rice for Brazil
and expand its business in that area.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mariajose Vera at 
 mvera1@bloomberg.net  